                            <comment id="12635726" author="koji" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2008 12:43:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch uses QueryParser.escape() code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12636077" author="koji" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2008 17:06:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll commit this in a few days if there is no objections.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12636084" author="ryantxu" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2008 17:27:38 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;but this has one BIG functional change...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;since we are not escaping whitespace, now stuff passed to escaper has to escape it explicitly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;that is, before, I could pass in the name &quot;David Bowie&quot;  and know that that would be the Term.  With these changes, I would have to pass in &quot;\&quot;David Bowie\&quot;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;perhaps we add ifWhitespace() then \char&lt;/p&gt;



</comment>
                            <comment id="12636620" author="koji" created="Fri, 3 Oct 2008 13:46:04 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;but this has one BIG functional change...&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Right. I added a new escape() method and moved escapeQueryChars() javadoc to the new method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12637326" author="koji" created="Tue, 7 Oct 2008 01:38:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 702314.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12637392" author="koji" created="Tue, 7 Oct 2008 06:55:40 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;since we are not escaping whitespace, now stuff passed to escaper has to escape it explicitly.&lt;br/&gt;
that is, before, I could pass in the name &quot;David Bowie&quot; and know that that would be the Term. With these changes, I would have to pass in &quot;\&quot;David Bowie\&quot;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
perhaps we add ifWhitespace() then \char&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 702355. Thanks Ryan!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
